hopobject.body: Your cash is being counted jax coco instagram Pixel overkill: “retina display” is the highest level of pixel density that the naked human eye can see from a given distance. The new Nexus 7 is even more dense than retina display, and if that sounds too good to be true, it is. The screen is denser than the human eye can see, without the assistance of a magnifying glass. What’s the point of it, then? There is none, except that when the iPad mini 2 arrives with retina display, Google can technically claim that the Nexus 7 is more pixel-dense. But you’d have to have better than 20-20 vision for that to matter.
